        <h2>About Him</h2>
        <p>
            Dr. A. P. J. Abdul Kalam (1931–2015) was an aerospace scientist,
            visionary leader, and the 11th President of India.
            Rising from humble beginnings, he inspired millions through
            his dedication, integrity, and passion for education and innovation.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Why He Inspires Me</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>He proved that dreams and discipline can change destinies.</li>
            <li>He dedicated his life to science and nation-building.</li>
            <li>He remained humble despite great achievements.</li>
            <li>He believed in lifelong learning and optimism.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Key Achievements</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Key contributor to India’s missile & space programs.</li>
            <li>Major role in Pokhran-II nuclear tests.</li>
            <li>Recipient of Bharat Ratna and other national honors.</li>
            <li>Author of inspiring books like <em>Wings of Fire</em>.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Inspirational Quote</h2>
